org.fluentjava.collections
Interface Enumerable<E>

Type Parameters:
E - Type of Elements.
All Superinterfaces:
ExtendedIterable<E>, Iterable<E>
All Known Subinterfaces:
FluentList<E>, FluentMap<K,V>, FluentSet<E>
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractEnumerable, Dictionary, Enumerator, ExtendedSet, ForwardingFluentList, ForwardingFluentMap, ForwardingFluentSet, Sequence
public interface Enumerable<E>
extends ExtendedIterable<E>

Implements a enumeration protocol. A class that implement this interface allow its elements to be operated on with closures. All exceptions caught while iterating are wrapped around the Runtime Exception EnumeratingException. Important: all arguments named closures will be coerced into a Closure using ClosureCoercion methods, and therefore, can throw ClosureCoercionException.

Similar to map(Object), but returns a list where the elements are pairs whose first element is the element from the Enumerable, and the second one is the result of the closure applied to such element.          Object closure)

Combines the elements of Enumerator by applying the closure to an accumulator value (memo) and each element in turn. At each step, memo is set to the value returned by the closure. The first form lets you supply an initial value for memo
